This paper is about misbehavior detection in vehicular networks, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of data analysis and machine learning techniques for misbehavior detection, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with cyber-physical systems, which is a subfield of systems and control (cs.SY).
